sp.p:
I'm glad of that—they left a long score unpaid. Now, I shouldn't mind if Ben
Binnacle was popped off; he was the only as one paid his shot afore he sailed;
and I've got his shore togs in keeping.

Not so; the money we have paid was Harry's, my earnings were trifling; and I
love him more for sacrificing the means of our marriage, than I did for earning
them; for that sacrifice was for you, my second father. (turning to
Harry) Why should we not struggle together as man and wife, as singly;
if you think my hand a reward for your noble devotion, take it—I will be yours,
even to-morrow.
